      "title": "DERM Approved 99% Grease Trap Efficiency Specialist in Miami",
      "slug": "derm-approved-99-grease-trap-efficiency-specialist-in-miami",
      "body": "<p>[caption id=\"attachment_241\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"300\"] We provide DERM approved grease traps for the 99% efficiency requirement[/caption]<br /><br />We design and Install DERM approved 99% Efficiency grease trap systems with sampling ports in Miami-Dade County and Broward County. DERM recently changed their requirements on the FOG Permits and the efficiency of the systems to be installed restaurants, bars, industrial and commercial projects to a 99% efficiency rate, making most of the current models in the market obsolete in South Florida. At <a href=\"http://fixmycodeviolation.com\">FixMyCodeViolation.com</a> we are a local design-build firm that can design, specify, process the permits and install the required 99% efficiency grease trap system that DERM now requires. We will get your business back on-line and DERM compliant to prevent fines and your business license being revoked.<br /><br />When we perform the calculations to specify your 99% DERM approved grease trap we take many factors into account such existing plumbing fixture units, number of meals served, carry out meals vs done in and a variety of other factors that apply. The size and flow rate of the grease trap specified can vary based on each of these factors but they must now all have a sampling port as required by DERM. The sampling port must be inspected by DERM during installation and will be inspected by DERM every year along with the grease trap on a yearly basis.<br /><br />Some 99% DERM approved grease trap systems require two units to be installed in-line to reach the required efficiency. The two unit installation adds cost to the installation as there is more material, labor and space required to accommodate the multi-unit assembly, however, the ultimate product will surely meet or exceed the current DERM 99% efficiency requirements for grease discharge systems.<br /><br />Schedule a free on-site consultation with us today so we can get started on helping you close out your DERM grease trap violation and stop the fines. You can find more information on our website at <a href=\"http://fixmycodeviolation.com\">www.FixMyCodeViolation.com</a> or call today to schedule your free appointment at 305-222-7784 and one of our in-house Architects, Engineers or General Contractor's will get you started.<br /><br /></p>",
